      "document_date": "2024-02-14",
      "extracted_text": "Birmingham Pathology Services \u2014 Laboratory Report\nDate of report: 14 Feb 2024\nLABORATORY REPORT\nPatient: Daniel Ofori\nDOB: 1968-03-22\nNHS Number: 999 200 0002\nSample type: Venous blood\nSample date: 12 Feb 2024\nRequesting clinician: Dr R. Patel (Diabetes Clinic)\nGlycaemic markers:\nHbA1c: 9.1 % (76 mmol/mol) [target <7.0 %]\nRandom glucose: 12.4 mmol/L [reference 4.0-7.8]\nRenal function:\nSodium: 139 mmol/L [135-145]\nPotassium: 4.4 mmol/L [3.5-5.0]\nUrea: 5.8 mmol/L [2.5-7.8]\nCreatinine: 88 umol/L [60-110]\neGFR: 74 mL/min/1.73m2 [>60]\nLipid profile:\nTotal cholesterol: 5.0 mmol/L\nLDL cholesterol: 3.0 mmol/L\nHDL cholesterol: 1.1 mmol/L\nTriglycerides: 1.9 mmol/L\nUrine albumin:\nAlbumin:creatinine ratio: 2.4 mg/mmol [<3.0]\nComment:\nGlycaemic control has further deteriorated since previous result (HbA1c 8.7% in September 2023). Renal\nfunction preserved with eGFR 74 mL/min/1.73m2 and ACR within normal range. Lipid profile acceptable.\nRecommend clinical review.",
      "wall_clock_seconds": 0.11
    }
